  "prompt": "How does death occur?",
  "response": "Death occurs when critical body systems permanently stop functioning. This can happen through various mechanisms:\n\n1. Cardiac death\n- Heart stops beating\n- No blood circulation\n- Oxygen can't reach vital organs\n\n2. Brain death\n- Complete and irreversible loss of brain function\n- No brain stem activity\n- Permanent loss of consciousness\n\n3. Common causes of death include:\n- Organ failure\n- Severe trauma\n- Terminal illness\n- Heart attack\n- Stroke\n- Advanced age\n- Significant physical damage\n\n4. Biological process involves:\n- Cellular breakdown\n- Oxygen deprivation\n- Systemic shutdown of bodily functions\n\n5. Medical determination involves:\n- Cessation of heartbeat\n- Lack of brain activity\n- Absence of respiratory function\n\nThe specific mechanism varies depending on individual circumstances and underlying health conditions.",
